[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: GHOST Knowledge Management Requirements
UID: GHOST-KNOWLEDGE-MANAGEMENT
VERSION: 0.1
OPTIONS:
  MARKUP: Text
  AUTO_LEVELS: On
  NODE_IN_TOC: True

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 1. Purpose and Scope

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This document defines the top-level requirements for GHOST Knowledge Management.

Knowledge Management is the document-evidence context path that begins after prompt preparation and ends when document evidence has been selected, condensed, and written into the shared SuperPrompt for final prompt composition.

Detailed ingestion, retrieval/reranking, and evidence-selection/condensation behavior is owned by child requirement files 41, 42, and 43.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-ROOT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Knowledge Management Scope
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall provide a Knowledge Management capability that transforms project documents into query-relevant, traceable document context for the current request.

The capability shall include document ingestion, document retrieval, optional reranking, semantic evidence selection, evidence condensation, and SuperPrompt write-back.

The capability shall not own prompt preprocessing, memory retrieval, memory recording, final answer generation, GUI rendering, or future guardrail enforcement.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SRS-FILE-TREE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-PRODUCT-NAME
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Product and Package Naming Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
The product described by this document shall be named GHOST.

The existing Python package namespace may remain ragstream in current source code and implementation paths.

Requirements shall not treat ragstream as the product identity.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-CHILD-DOCUMENTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Knowledge Management Child Documents
STATEMENT: >>>
Knowledge Management shall be decomposed into these child requirement documents:

1. 41_document_ingestion.sdoc.
2. 42_document_retrieval_and_reranking.sdoc.
3. 43_evidence_selection_and_condensation.sdoc.

Each child document shall own its detailed atomic requirements and shall inherit from the Knowledge Management root requirement.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-CURRENT-CAPABILITIES
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Executable Knowledge Capabilities
STATEMENT: >>>
The current executable Knowledge Management baseline shall include:
- project-based raw-document ingestion;
- deterministic content hashing and manifest comparison;
- overlapping character-based chunking;
- dense OpenAI embeddings and persistent Chroma storage;
- optional SPLADE sparse encoding and storage;
- query projection and deterministic query splitting;
- dense candidate generation;
- optional SPLADE rescoring and weighted reciprocal-rank fusion;
- optional ColBERT reranking and a second weighted reciprocal-rank fusion;
- A3 usefulness classification and deterministic useful-only selection;
- A4 three-call evidence classification and condensation;
- document evidence write-back into SuperPrompt.

Unimplemented knowledge graphs, cross-context overlap removal, A5, guardrails, and background synchronization agents shall not be presented as current Knowledge Management behavior.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-REQUIREMENT-NATURE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Requirement Nature
STATEMENT: >>>
This document and its child documents shall define required behavior, interfaces, constraints, and verification criteria.

They shall not be written as implementation-status reports, design diaries, or speculative feature catalogs.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 2. Functional Architecture and Responsibility Boundaries

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The conceptual GHOST context-generation architecture is:

PreProcessing
-> Knowledge Management and Memory Management as logically independent context paths
-> Final Prompt Composition

Knowledge Management contains internal stages but is one top-level document-evidence capability.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-ARCHITECTURE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Knowledge Management Architectural Position
STATEMENT: >>>
Knowledge Management shall receive a prepared SuperPrompt from PreProcessing and shall produce document-derived supporting context for final prompt composition.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-INTERNAL-STAGES
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Internal Knowledge Management Stages
STATEMENT: >>>
Document ingestion, retrieval, reranking, A3 evidence selection, and A4 condensation shall be modeled as internal Knowledge Management functions rather than separate top-level GHOST pipelines.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ARCHITECTURE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-OLD-PIPELINE-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Old Eight-Stage Pipeline Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
The former learning-oriented eight-stage pipeline model shall not define the current top-level requirements hierarchy.

Legacy stage names may remain in code, lifecycle values, logs, metrics, and diagnostic views when they accurately identify internal processing steps.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ARCHITECTURE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-PREPROCESS-DEPENDENCY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: PreProcessing Dependency
STATEMENT: >>>
Knowledge Management shall consume the structured request and effective retrieval-query state prepared under 30_preprocessing_prompt_functions.sdoc.

Knowledge Management shall not reparse the original raw user prompt or repeat A2 prompt shaping.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ARCHITECTURE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-MEMORY-PEER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory Management Peer Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
Knowledge Management and Memory Management shall be treated as peer context-generation paths.

Knowledge Management shall not require the result of Memory Management in order to retrieve, rerank, select, or condense document evidence.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ARCHITECTURE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-NO-MEMORY-MUTATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Memory-State Mutation
STATEMENT: >>>
Knowledge Management shall not create, edit, tag, persist, retrieve, score, compress, or merge MemoryRecord data.

Memory-specific behavior shall remain owned by 50_memory_management.sdoc and its child files.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-MEMORY-PEER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-PROMPT-COMPOSITION-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Final Prompt Composition Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
Knowledge Management shall produce document context artifacts but shall not generate the final user-facing answer.

The final prompt-composition capability shall decide how the current request, document context, memory context, attachments, and later policy blocks are assembled for the answer model.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ARCHITECTURE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-AGENT-STACK-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Agent Stack Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 and A4 shall use the neutral Agent Stack contracts defined in 20_agent_stack.sdoc.

This requirement family shall own A3/A4 functional semantics, deterministic processing, evidence decisions, and SuperPrompt write-back without duplicating generic AgentFactory, AgentPrompt, or LLMClient requirements.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ARCHITECTURE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-CONTROLLER-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Controller Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
The application controller may coordinate ingestion, retrieval, reranking, A3, and A4 calls.

The controller shall not absorb document loading, hashing, chunking, scoring, fusion, classification, condensation, or evidence-selection business rules.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ARCHITECTURE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-GUI-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: GUI Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
The GUI may initiate Knowledge Management operations, select projects, expose optional-stage controls, and display stage results.

Detailed GUI layout, widget state, session state, and action behavior shall remain owned by interface requirement files.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ARCHITECTURE

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 3. End-to-End Knowledge Flow and Dependencies

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The Knowledge Management flow separates offline/project ingestion from per-request context generation.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-OFFLINE-ONLINE-SEPARATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Ingestion and Query-Time Separation
STATEMENT: >>>
Document ingestion shall prepare persistent project indexes independently of any individual user request.

Retrieval, reranking, A3, and A4 shall operate at request time against the active project and current SuperPrompt.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-FLOW-INGEST
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Ingestion Output Dependency
STATEMENT: >>>
Document Retrieval shall depend on successfully created project document stores and the raw source files needed for chunk hydration.

A project without the required dense store or raw-document source shall not be represented as fully retrievable.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-OFFLINE-ONLINE-SEPARATION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-FLOW-QUERY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Prepared Query Dependency
STATEMENT: >>>
Document Retrieval shall consume the effective query projection derived from the current SuperPrompt and ActiveBrief routing state.

A suppressed document-retrieval route shall not be replaced by an unrelated fallback query.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-OFFLINE-ONLINE-SEPARATION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-FLOW-RETRIEVAL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Retrieval Candidate Contract
STATEMENT: >>>
Document Retrieval shall write hydrated candidate chunks, ordered retrieval views, and current selection identifiers into the same SuperPrompt.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-OFFLINE-ONLINE-SEPARATION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-FLOW-RERANK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Reranking Dependency
STATEMENT: >>>
Real reranking shall consume the candidates produced by Document Retrieval.

When reranking is bypassed, downstream evidence selection shall receive an explicit retrieval-order passthrough rather than fabricated ColBERT evidence.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-OFFLINE-ONLINE-SEPARATION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-FLOW-A3
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Dependency
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 evidence selection shall consume reranked candidates when available and shall otherwise consume the documented retrieval passthrough candidate view.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-OFFLINE-ONLINE-SEPARATION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-FLOW-A4
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Dependency
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 condensation shall consume only A3 candidates classified as useful and successfully mapped to hydrated document chunks.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-OFFLINE-ONLINE-SEPARATION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-FLOW-HANDOFF
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Knowledge Context Handoff
STATEMENT: >>>
At Knowledge Management completion, the SuperPrompt shall contain the authoritative condensed document-context artifact, final retained document identifiers, stage views, and traceability metadata required by final prompt composition.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-OFFLINE-ONLINE-SEPARATION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-SEQUENTIAL-CURRENT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Sequential Invocation
STATEMENT: >>>
The current controller may invoke document retrieval and memory retrieval sequentially.

Sequential invocation shall not be interpreted as a semantic dependency between their results.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-MEMORY-PEER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-PARALLEL-FUTURE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Future Concurrent Coordination Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
Future orchestration may execute Knowledge Management and Memory Management concurrently when their input contracts and shared-state safety permit it.

Concurrent execution shall be treated as a future orchestration refinement and shall not be required by the current Knowledge Management baseline.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-SEQUENTIAL-CURRENT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 4. Shared Knowledge Artifacts and SuperPrompt Contract

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
SuperPrompt remains the authoritative per-request state carrier for document evidence.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-SUPERPROMPT-AUTHORITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: SuperPrompt Authority
STATEMENT: >>>
Knowledge Management shall mutate and return the same active SuperPrompt instance rather than creating an independent document-context state owner.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-BASE-CHUNKS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Hydrated Base Chunk Contract
STATEMENT: >>>
SuperPrompt.base_context_chunks shall contain hydrated document Chunk objects for the current request in the applicable retrieval order.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-SUPERPROMPT-AUTHORITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-STAGE-VIEWS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Stage View Contract
STATEMENT: >>>
SuperPrompt.views_by_stage shall retain ordered stage-specific rows sufficient to distinguish retrieval, reranked, A3, and A4 outcomes.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-SUPERPROMPT-AUTHORITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-FINAL-IDS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Final Selection Identifier Contract
STATEMENT: >>>
SuperPrompt.final_selection_ids shall represent the ordered document identifiers currently surviving the latest completed Knowledge Management stage.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-SUPERPROMPT-AUTHORITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-SCTX
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Condensed Document Context Contract
STATEMENT: >>>
SuperPrompt.S_CTX_MD shall contain the A4-condensed document evidence summary when A4 succeeds.

S_CTX_MD shall be internal supporting context and shall not be written as a user-facing final answer.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-SUPERPROMPT-AUTHORITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-EXTRAS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Diagnostic Extras Contract
STATEMENT: >>>
Knowledge Management may write retrieval, reranking, A3, and A4 diagnostic metadata into SuperPrompt.extras.

Diagnostic fields shall not become an alternative source of truth when an authoritative typed SuperPrompt field exists.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-SUPERPROMPT-AUTHORITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-STAGE-HISTORY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Lifecycle History Contract
STATEMENT: >>>
Each completed request-time Knowledge Management step shall update the SuperPrompt lifecycle stage and append its stage identifier to history_of_stages.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-SUPERPROMPT-AUTHORITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-PROVENANCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Document Provenance Preservation
STATEMENT: >>>
Every retained document evidence item shall remain traceable to its stable chunk identifier, project-relative source path, source-version hash, and chunk index when those values exist in the ingestion metadata.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-SUPERPROMPT-AUTHORITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-RAW-CONDENSED-SEPARATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Raw and Condensed Evidence Separation
STATEMENT: >>>
Raw hydrated chunks, stage rankings, semantic usefulness decisions, and condensed context shall remain distinguishable artifacts.

A condensed summary shall not silently replace or rewrite the raw stored document chunks.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-SUPERPROMPT-AUTHORITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-PROMPT-RENDER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Prompt Preview Projection
STATEMENT: >>>
The central SuperPrompt projector may render raw document evidence before A4 and shall render condensed document context after A4 according to the final prompt-composition contract.

Knowledge Management components shall not independently create competing prompt-preview formats.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-SUPERPROMPT-AUTHORITY

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 5. Independence from Memory and Future Context Coordination

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Knowledge and memory context are currently generated separately and combined only in the final prompt projection.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-INDEPENDENT-SELECTION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Independent Evidence Selection
STATEMENT: >>>
Document candidate generation, reranking, A3 selection, and A4 condensation shall use document evidence and the current request without requiring raw memory candidates or synthesized memory context.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-MEMORY-PEER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-NO-CROSS-PRUNING
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Current Cross-Context Pruning
STATEMENT: >>>
The current Knowledge Management baseline shall not remove document evidence because similar information exists in Memory Management output.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-INDEPENDENT-SELECTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-NO-MEMORY-IN-A3
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Memory Exclusion
STATEMENT: >>>
A3 shall classify document candidates only.

Memory candidate filtering and memory-context synthesis shall remain outside A3.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-INDEPENDENT-SELECTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-NO-MEMORY-IN-A4
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A4 Memory Exclusion
STATEMENT: >>>
A4 shall condense selected document evidence only.

A4 shall not condense MemoryContextPack content or synthesize a joint document-memory context in the current baseline.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-INDEPENDENT-SELECTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-FUTURE-OVERLAP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Future Document-Memory Overlap Control
STATEMENT: >>>
A future context-coordination capability may detect and remove information overlap between condensed document context and synthesized memory context.

That future behavior shall be specified outside 40–43 and shall not be implied as current Knowledge Management behavior.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-INDEPENDENT-SELECTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-FUTURE-KG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Future Knowledge Graph Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
Future knowledge-graph extraction, graph retrieval, graph-memory coordination, and Blackboard integration shall require separate approved requirements.

They shall not be inserted into the current document-ingestion or document-retrieval contracts without an explicit change.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-INDEPENDENT-SELECTION

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 6. Configuration and Current/Future Implementation Boundary

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Operational tuning values affect quality, latency, and cost and therefore require explicit configuration governance.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-CONFIG-AUTHORITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Runtime Configuration Authority
STATEMENT: >>>
Operationally tunable Knowledge Management parameters shall be represented in versioned JSON runtime configuration rather than remaining permanently distributed as Python literals.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-CONFIG-SCOPE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Knowledge Configuration Scope
STATEMENT: >>>
The configuration target shall include at least:
- chunk and query window sizes and overlaps;
- retrieval candidate limits;
- embedding and sparse-model identifiers;
- score floors;
- p-norm aggregation values;
- RRF constants and branch weights;
- reranker model, candidate limit, and runtime device;
- A3 candidate and useful-selection limits;
- A4 candidate and output-token limits;
- optional-stage enable/bypass switches;
- version-cleanup and tombstone policies.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-CONFIG-AUTHORITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-CONFIG-VALIDATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Configuration Validation
STATEMENT: >>>
Knowledge Management configuration shall be validated before use.

Invalid ranges, missing required paired settings, incompatible chunking values, invalid weights, unknown models, and non-positive limits shall fail explicitly or use a documented safe default.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-CONFIG-AUTHORITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-EFFECTIVE-CONFIG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Effective Configuration Observability
STATEMENT: >>>
Every Knowledge Management run shall make the effective values of quality-, cost-, and latency-relevant configuration observable through logs, diagnostics, or stage metadata.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-CONFIG-AUTHORITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-TRANSITIONAL-CONSTANTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Transitional Code Constants
STATEMENT: >>>
Until a tuning parameter has been migrated to JSON configuration, the current implementation may retain an explicit code default.

Such a value shall be documented as transitional and shall not be falsely described as runtime-configurable.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-CONFIG-AUTHORITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-NO-HIDDEN-TUNING
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Hidden Tuning Changes
STATEMENT: >>>
A change to retrieval weights, candidate limits, score floors, chunking values, model identifiers, or evidence budgets shall be treated as a controlled behavior/configuration change rather than an undocumented code edit.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-CONFIG-AUTHORITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-CURRENT-FUTURE-LABEL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current and Future Capability Labeling
STATEMENT: >>>
Current executable behavior and approved future configuration migration shall remain explicitly distinguishable in requirements, architecture, implementation status, and tests.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-CONFIG-AUTHORITY

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 7. Error Handling, Logging, and Observability

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Knowledge Management failures must remain visible and must not be converted into fabricated evidence.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-NO-FABRICATED-EVIDENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Fabricated Document Evidence
STATEMENT: >>>
A missing project, failed embedding request, missing index, invalid model output, broken source path, or empty evidence set shall not be represented as successful document evidence.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-ERROR-OWNERSHIP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Error Ownership
STATEMENT: >>>
Each component shall validate errors that belong to its own boundary and shall return or raise enough context for the controller to report the failed operation.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-NO-FABRICATED-EVIDENCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-PARTIAL-DEGRADATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Controlled Optional-Branch Degradation
STATEMENT: >>>
Failure or absence of an explicitly optional retrieval branch may degrade to a documented fallback when that fallback preserves the downstream contract.

The fallback shall be distinguishable from successful execution of the optional branch.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-NO-FABRICATED-EVIDENCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-LOG-LEVELS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Knowledge Logging Levels
STATEMENT: >>>
Knowledge Management shall provide concise public stage status and more detailed internal/developer diagnostics without exposing confidential full prompts or document contents by default.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-LATENCY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Stage Latency Observability
STATEMENT: >>>
Request-time Knowledge Management stages shall expose sufficient timing data to analyze retrieval, reranking, A3, A4, and provider latency independently.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-COUNTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Candidate Count Observability
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall expose candidate counts and retained counts at retrieval, reranking, A3, and A4 boundaries.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-MODEL-USAGE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Model and Token Observability
STATEMENT: >>>
LLM- or model-backed Knowledge Management steps shall expose the effective model identifier and available usage metadata through the owning logging/metrics facilities.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-LOGGING-REFERENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Logging Ownership Reference
STATEMENT: >>>
Detailed sink, confidentiality, retention, formatting, and audit requirements shall be owned by 81_logging_textforge_raglog.sdoc.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 8. Quality, Determinism, and Performance Requirements

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Knowledge Management combines deterministic data processing with bounded model-assisted evidence classification and synthesis.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-DETERMINISTIC-OPERATIONS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Deterministic Knowledge Operations
STATEMENT: >>>
File hashing, manifest diffing, chunk identifiers, query splitting, score aggregation, ranking fusion, local-id mapping, result regrouping, and stage write-back shall be deterministic for identical inputs and effective configuration.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-MODEL-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Model-Assisted Operation Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
Dense embedding, SPLADE encoding, ColBERT scoring, A3 classification, and A4 condensation may use external or local models.

Model outputs shall be subjected to the deterministic validation and write-back rules owned by their components.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-STABLE-TIES
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Stable Tie Resolution
STATEMENT: >>>
Ranked document results with equal effective scores shall use a stable deterministic fallback such as chunk identifier order.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-DETERMINISTIC-OPERATIONS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-NO-CHUNK-MUTATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Stored Chunk Integrity
STATEMENT: >>>
Query-time cleaning, prompt sanitization, classification, and condensation shall not mutate the persisted document source or stored canonical chunk text.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-BOUNDED-CANDIDATES
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Bounded Candidate Processing
STATEMENT: >>>
Every request-time model-assisted stage shall operate on an explicit bounded candidate set to control latency, cost, and prompt size.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-QUALITY-EVALUATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Optional Branch Quality Evaluation
STATEMENT: >>>
SPLADE and ColBERT branches shall remain optional and independently evaluable until measured evidence supports a stronger mandatory quality claim.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-PERFORMANCE-NO-QUALITY-LIE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Performance and Quality Truthfulness
STATEMENT: >>>
A performance optimization or bypass shall not be described as quality-equivalent unless verified against representative retrieval cases and acceptance criteria.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-REPRODUCIBILITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Knowledge Run Reproducibility
STATEMENT: >>>
The project version, effective configuration, model identifiers, source hashes, and stable chunk identifiers shall be sufficient to reproduce or audit a Knowledge Management result to the practical extent supported by external model determinism.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 9. Traceability and Sibling Requirement Ownership

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This file provides capability-level ownership and delegates atomic behavior to child and sibling requirement files.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-INGESTION-REFERENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Document Ingestion Ownership
STATEMENT: >>>
Detailed source discovery, hashing, manifest, chunking, embedding, storage, cleanup, and ingestion statistics requirements shall be owned by 41_document_ingestion.sdoc.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-RETRIEVAL-REFERENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Retrieval and Reranking Ownership
STATEMENT: >>>
Detailed query splitting, dense retrieval, SPLADE rescoring, RRF fusion, hydration, ColBERT reranking, passthrough, and retrieval write-back requirements shall be owned by 42_document_retrieval_and_reranking.sdoc.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-EVIDENCE-REFERENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Evidence Selection and Condensation Ownership
STATEMENT: >>>
Detailed A3 classification, useful-selection, A4 thematic grouping, fallback, condensation, and evidence write-back requirements shall be owned by 43_evidence_selection_and_condensation.sdoc.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-PREPROCESS-REFERENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: PreProcessing Ownership Reference
STATEMENT: >>>
Prompt parsing, ActiveBrief relation routing, A2 PromptShaper, and effective retrieval-query preparation shall remain owned by 30_preprocessing_prompt_functions.sdoc.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-MEMORY-REFERENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory Ownership Reference
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory recording, ingestion, retrieval, scoring, compression, ActiveBrief maintenance, and Memory Context synthesis shall remain owned by the Memory Management requirement family.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-PROMPT-BUILDER-REFERENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Final Composition Ownership Reference
STATEMENT: >>>
The final assembly of current request, document context, memory context, recent conversation, attachments, and later policies shall remain owned by the final prompt-composition requirement.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-FUTURE-REFERENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Future Capability Ownership Reference
STATEMENT: >>>
A5, guardrails, Hard Rules, knowledge graphs, Blackboard coordination, document-memory overlap removal, and background requirement-code synchronization shall remain owned by future requirement files.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-CODE-TRACEABILITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Code Traceability Direction
STATEMENT: >>>
Knowledge Management implementation units shall be traceable to the deepest applicable requirement UID under files 41–43.

The top-level Knowledge Management root shall not replace atomic child ownership for code and test mapping.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-CHANGE-SYNC
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Requirement-Code Synchronization
STATEMENT: >>>
An approved behavior change affecting Knowledge Management interfaces, constraints, persistence, rankings, stage artifacts, or observable outcomes shall update requirements, architecture, implementation traceability, and verification together.

Pure internal refactoring that preserves approved behavior shall not require artificial requirement changes.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ROOT

