[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 10. Acceptance Criteria

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
These criteria validate the top-level Knowledge Management architecture without duplicating detailed child acceptance tests.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-AC-HIERARCHY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Knowledge Hierarchy
STATEMENT: >>>
The approved requirements set shall show PreProcessing followed by peer Knowledge and Memory context paths and final prompt composition, while retrieval, reranking, A3, and A4 remain internal Knowledge Management functions.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-ARCHITECTURE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-AC-INGESTION-HANDOFF
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Ingestion-to-Retrieval Handoff
STATEMENT: >>>
Given a successfully ingested project, its raw files, stable chunk metadata, dense store, and optional sparse store shall be sufficient for document retrieval and hydration.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-FLOW-INGEST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-AC-INDEPENDENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Memory Independence
STATEMENT: >>>
Given identical prepared prompt and project state, document retrieval and evidence selection shall not require Memory Management output to execute.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-INDEPENDENT-SELECTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-AC-STAGE-ARTIFACTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Stage Artifact Separation
STATEMENT: >>>
After retrieval, reranking, A3, and A4, the SuperPrompt shall preserve distinguishable stage views and the current final-selection identifiers.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-STAGE-VIEWS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-AC-SCTX
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Condensed Context Handoff
STATEMENT: >>>
After successful A4 completion, S_CTX_MD shall contain internal document supporting context and final prompt composition shall be able to render it without treating it as the user request.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-SCTX

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-AC-EMPTY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Empty Evidence Integrity
STATEMENT: >>>
Given no usable document evidence, Knowledge Management shall produce an explicit empty or skipped state and shall not fabricate S_CTX_MD content.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-NO-FABRICATED-EVIDENCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-AC-CONFIG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Configuration Governance
STATEMENT: >>>
Every migrated tuning parameter shall be read from validated versioned JSON configuration and its effective value shall be observable for the run.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-CONFIG-AUTHORITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-AC-TRANSITION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Transitional Constant Truth
STATEMENT: >>>
A parameter still hard-coded in Python shall be documented as a current constant and shall not be reported as JSON-controlled until the implementation consumes the JSON value.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-TRANSITIONAL-CONSTANTS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-AC-PROVENANCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Evidence Provenance
STATEMENT: >>>
Every final retained document identifier shall map to a hydrated chunk and to source-version metadata sufficient to locate the originating project file and chunk index.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-PROVENANCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-AC-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: No Future Feature Leakage
STATEMENT: >>>
The current Knowledge Management requirements shall not claim implemented document-memory overlap removal, knowledge-graph retrieval, Blackboard coordination, A5, guardrails, or background synchronization agents.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-FUTURE-REFERENCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-KM-AC-SYNC
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Requirement-Code Consistency
STATEMENT: >>>
A release baseline shall not be accepted when approved Knowledge Management requirements contradict implemented stage order, artifact semantics, configuration authority, or evidence-selection behavior.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-KM-CHANGE-SYNC

[[/SECTION]]
